    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n486" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλάομαι</span></b> , imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλόω</span>, ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἠλώμην,
            ἀλώμην</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλήθην</span>, pf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλάλημαι, ἀλαλήμενος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">wander,
            rove, roam</span>, of adventurers, freebooters, mendicants, and
          homeless or lost persons. The perf. is only more intensive in meaning
          than the present, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.370</span></i>,
          etc.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
